    "body": "<!-- Thank you for your contribution! Please follow these guidelines to enhance your pull request. If anything is unclear, submit your PR and reach out to maintainers for assistance. Join our Slack community at https://slack.sglang.io to discuss further. -->\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\nWhen the batch dimension of the query does not match `qo_indptr[-1]` in `BatchMLAPagedAttentionWrapper` (as described in FlashInfer issue #[2236](https://github.com/flashinfer-ai/flashinfer/issues/2236)), an invalid memory access can occur as below. \r\n```\r\n  File \"/workspace/build/aot/generated/batch_mla_attention_dtype_q_bf16_dtype_kv_bf16_dtype_o_bf16_dtype_idx_i32_head_dim_ckv_512_head_dim_kpe_64_profiler_False/batch_mla_run.cu\", line 123, in BatchMLAPagedAttentionRun(tvm::ffi::TensorView, tvm::ffi::TensorView, tvm::ffi::Array<long int>, tvm::ffi::TensorView, tvm::ffi::TensorView, tvm::ffi::TensorView, tvm::ffi::TensorView, tvm::ffi::TensorView, tvm::ffi::TensorView, tvm::ffi::Optional<tvm::ffi::TensorView>, int64_t, int64_t, int64_t, double, bool)::<lambda()>\r\nRuntimeError: Check failed: (status == cudaSuccess) is false: Failed to run MLA, error: an illegal memory access was encountered\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe root cause is that the forward_metadata—including `qo_indptr`—is not updated in the TRTLLM MLA backend, leading to inconsistent metadata being used during execution.\r\n\r\n## Modifications\r\n\r\n<!-- Detail the changes made in this pull request. -->\r\n\r\n## Accuracy Tests\r\n\r\n<!-- If this pull request affects model outputs (e.g., changes to the kernel or model forward code), provide accuracy test results. -->\r\n\r\n## Benchmarking and Profiling\r\n\r\n```\r\nCUDA_LAUNCH_BLOCKING=1 \\\r\nSGLANG_MOE_NVFP4_DISPATCH=1 \\\r\nHF_TOKEN=<your token> \\\r\npython -m sglang.launch_server \\\r\n  --model-path nvidia/DeepSeek-R1-0528-FP4-v2 \\\r\n  --trust-remote-code \\\r\n  --kv-cache-dtype fp8_e4m3 \\\r\n  --attention-backend trtllm_mla \\\r\n  --quantization modelopt_fp4 \\\r\n  --moe-runner-backend flashinfer_cutlass \\\r\n  --disable-radix-cache \\\r\n  --disable-chunked-prefix-cache \\\r\n  --disable-shared-experts-fusion \\\r\n  --disable-cuda-graph \\\r\n  --stream-interval 50 \\\r\n  --decode-log-interval 1000 \\\r\n  --watchdog-timeout 1000000 \\\r\n  --context-length 2176 \\\r\n  --max-total-tokens 131072 \\\r\n  --max-prefill-tokens 32768 \\\r\n  --chunked-prefill-size 65536 \\\r\n  --max-running-requests 30000 \\\r\n  --mem-fraction-static 0.84 \\\r\n  --enable-dp-attention \\\r\n  --tp-size 4 \\\r\n  --dp-size 4 \\\r\n  --ep-size 4 \\\r\n  --eplb-algorithm deepseek \\\r\n  --speculative-algorithm EAGLE \\\r\n  --speculative-num-steps 1 \\\r\n  --speculative-eagle-topk 1 \\\r\n  --speculative-num-draft-tokens 2\r\n\r\nclient:\r\npython3 benchmark/gsm8k/bench_sglang.py --num-shots 8 --num-questions 1319 --parallel 1319 --port=30000\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe flashinfer attn backend:\r\n```\r\nAccuracy: 0.961\r\nInvalid: 0.000\r\nLatency: 132.733s\r\nOutput throughput: 1099.874 token/s\r\n```\r\ntrtllm_mla attn backend:\r\n```\r\nAccuracy: 0.959\r\nInvalid: 0.000\r\nLatency: 130.433 s\r\nOutput throughput: 1133.730 token/s\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Checklist\r\n\r\n- [ ] Format your code according to the [Format code with pre-commit](https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#format-code-with-pre-commit).\r\n- [ ] Add unit tests according to the [Run and add unit tests](https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#run-and-add-unit-tests).\r\n- [ ] Update documentation according to [Write documentations](https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#write-documentations).\r\n- [ ] Provide accuracy and speed benchmark results according to [Test the accuracy](https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#test-the-accuracy) and [Benchmark the speed](https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#benchmark-the-speed).\r\n- [ ] Follow the SGLang code style [guidance](https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#code-style-guidance).\r\n- [ ] Work with maintainers to merge your PR. See the [PR Merge Process](https://github.com/sgl-project/sglang/blob/main/.github/MAINTAINER.md#pull-request-merge-process)\r\n",
